 <title>23 Chinese Cities Commit to Peak Carbon Emissions by 2030</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/23-chinese-cities-commit-peak-carbon-emissions-2030</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/climate_leaders_summit_2016_0.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;160&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Wee Kean Fong        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This post &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/06/23-chinese-cities-commit-peak-carbon-emissions-2030&quot;&gt;originally appeared&lt;/a&gt; on WRI&amp;#8217;s insights blog.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More than &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.who.int/gho/urban_health/situation_trends/urban_population_growth_text/en/&quot;&gt;half the world&amp;rsquo;s people live in cities&lt;/a&gt;, and cities are responsible for more than 70 percent of all energy-related carbon dioxide emissions on Earth. These dramatic statistics mean &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2015/01/why-cities-are-solution-climate-change-qa-ani-dasgupta&quot;&gt;cities have a critical role to play in addressing climate change&lt;/a&gt;. This is especially crucial in China, where fast-growing metropolitan areas like Chengdu &amp;ndash; with a population of 14 million &amp;#8211; have become engines for economic, scientific and technological progress. Until recently, Chengdu has not focused on reducing greenhouse gas emissions, even as it emphasized sustainable development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/23-chinese-cities-commit-peak-carbon-emissions-2030&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
