&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This post &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/04/carbon-capture-and-storage-prospects-after-paris&quot;&gt;originally appeared&lt;/a&gt; on WRI&amp;#8217;s Insights blog:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Momentum for climate action &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/04/commitment-action-signs-progress-paris-climate-talks&quot;&gt;has surged&lt;/a&gt; since the Paris Agreement in December, with increased investment in clean, renewable energy and new energy technologies. But will the Agreement give a needed boost to carbon capture and storage? Known as CCS, this suite of technologies aims to keep climate-warming carbon dioxide out of the atmosphere, acting as a bridge to a lower-carbon future.&lt;/p&gt;
